description: Enforce repository workflow conventions for PrepDocente EC
alwaysApply: false
---

# Branches

- Treat `develop` as the default integration branch and `main` as production-only.
- Before creating an agent-managed branch, run `git fetch --prune origin`, switch to `develop`, and fast-forward from `origin/develop` unless told otherwise.
- Never commit directly on `develop` or `main`; create a work branch first.
- Prune local branches whose upstream no longer exists after confirming they have no unique unmerged work.
- Use branch names: `feat/<scope>`, `fix/<scope>`, `bug/<scope>`, `chore/<scope>`, `refactor/<scope>`, `docs/<scope>`, `test/<scope>`, or `hotfix/<scope>`.
- Never delete or force-push `develop` or `main`.

# Commits

- Use Conventional Commits with gitmojis, e.g. `feat(simulator): ✨ add dimension 1 timer`.
- Keep subjects imperative and under 72 characters.
- STRICTLY group commits by one specific logical task: tests, docs, CI, refactor, simulator, dashboard, etc.
- MUST NOT bundle unrelated workstreams in one commit (e.g., do not mix UI changes with CI changes).
- A gitmoji MUST appear right after the colon in the commit subject to easily identify the logical task.

# Pull Requests

- Never push directly to `develop` or `main`; push feature branches and open a PR.
- Before creating a PR, ensure the branch includes the latest `origin/develop`.
- Base PRs on `develop` unless explicitly doing a release or hotfix to `main`.
- Follow `.cursor/rules/pr-format.mdc` for PR title, body, and assignment.
